ion="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link EFT is a secure way to deliver your UIC gifts directly and automatically from your bank to the University of Illinois Foundation. As with online giving, EFT donations allow us to minimize administrative expenses. When you make an EFT gift, your bank disburses the funds automatically according to your instructions, and until you decide to stop. You may extend your contribution into installments over the entire year. To make your gifts via EFT, simply download, complete and return the EFT Authorization Form Either fax the authorization form to (217) 333–5577 or mail it to: Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link UIC employees can instruct the University to withhold a minimum contribution of $5 per month for a period of time (no less than three installments) or until you opt to discontinue the withholding. To make your gifts via payroll deduction, please visit uif.uillinois.edu/payroll-deductions Heading link xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"? Copy link Give to UIC Back to main content Give Now Priorities Support Student Success Empower Faculty Drive Discoveries Connect to Communities Support a College or Unit Ways to Give Types of Giving UIC Corporate and Foundation Relations For Corporations For Faculty and Staff For Foundations Understanding Giving Donor Advised Funds Gift Planning Giving Strategies How to Give University of Illinois Chicago Contact 815 W. Van Buren Street, Suite 400, Rice Building, MC 002, Chicago, IL 60607 Phone: (312) 413-8272 advance@uic.edu Social Media Accounts xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Facebook xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Twitter xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? Instagram xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"? YouTube UIC.edu links UIC.edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Safe Mobile App UIC Today UI Health Veterans Affair